    "While R e, R g and asphericity are relatively coarse-grain, they can offer insight into the molecular conformations accessible to an IDR, as well as provide hints at the types of intramolecular interactions that may also be relevant for intermolecular interactions (especially in the context of low-complexity sequences) [16] [17] [18].",
